ped%20The%20Taliban%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESushmita%20Banerjee%20was%20all%20of%2025%20when%20she%20met%20Jaambaz%20Khan%2C%20an%20Afghan%20moneylender%2C%20at%20a%20theatre%20rehearsal%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20West%20Bengal.%20It%20was%201986.%20Sushmita's%20friend%20played%20Cupid.%20Sushmita%20and%20Jaambaz%20met%20once%20a%20week%2C%20for%20an%20hour%2C%20at%20Flury's%20in%20the%20city.%20Over%20coffee%20and%20a%20pastry%20shared%20between%20the%20two%20of%20them%2C%20they%20got%20to%20%26quot%3Bknow%26quot%3B%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20enough%2C%20lamented%20Banerjee%20later%2C%20when%20she%20found%20herself%20in%20Kharana%2C%20deep%20inside%20Taliban-ruled%20Afghanistan%2C%20where%20Jaambaz%20took%20her%20after%20their%20secret%20wedding%20under%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20on%20July%202%2C%201988.%20Sushmita%20was%20a%20%26quot%3BBengali%20Brahmin%26quot%3B%20girl.%20She%20married%20%26quot%3BAfghan%20Muslim%26quot%3B%20Jaambaz%20against%20her%20parents'%20wishes.%20When%20her%20parents%20discovered%20the%20marriage%2C%20they%20tried%20to%20get%20them%20divorced%3B%20but%20in%20vain.%20Sushmita%20left%20Kolkata%20for%20Kabul%20with%20Jaambaz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushmita%20was%2027%20when%20she%20married%20Jaambaz.%20She%20did%20not%20convert%20to%20Islam.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20three%20years%20after%20she%20arrived%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Jaambaz%20was%20gone.%20He%20had%20left%20Afghanistan%20to%20go%20back%20to%20India%2C%20where%20he%20had%20his%20moneylending%20business.%20Sushmita%20wasn't%20informed.%20He%20was%20gone.%3B%20just%20like%20that%3B%20as%20she%20wondered%20if%20the%20Taliban%20had%20done%20away%20with%20his%20head%20for%20marrying%20a%20Hindu%20woman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BHe%20left%20of%20his%20own%20accord.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushmita%20stayed%20behind%20in%20the%20province%20of%20Paktika%2C%20living%20a%20nightmare%2C%20as%20the%20Taliban%20combed%20the%20streets%20and%20executed%20any%20woman%20who%20dared%20to%20defy%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20many%20years%20before%20Indian%20woman%20Uzma%20Ahmed%20found%20herself%20living%20a%20similar%20nightmare%20in%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%20in%20Pakistan%3B%20and%20the%20story%20of%20whose%20escape%20is%20on%20the%20big%20screen%20in%20the%20John%20Abraham%20and%20Sadia%20Khateeb-starrer%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Diplomat%3C%2Fem%3E%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUzma%20called%20herself%20lucky%20to%20have%20got%20back%20to%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Sushmita%2C%20life%20played%20out%20a%20little%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EKabuliwala's%20Bengali%20Bride%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushmita%20Banerjee%20shot%20to%20fame%20in%201995%2C%20when%20the%20memoir%20of%20her%20daring%20escape%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20the%20Taliban%20made%20headlines%20in%20Bengal%20and%20the%20country.%20In%20%3Cem%3EKabuliwala's%20Bengali%20Bride%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EKabuliwala's%20Bangali%20Bou%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Bengali%2C%201995)%2C%20Banerjee%20recounted%20in%20detail%20how%20her%20days%20in%20the%20mountains%20of%20Afghanistan%20were%20measured%20out%20in%20screams%20and%20torture%20by%20her%20in-laws%20once%20Jaambaz%20was%20gone.%20Khan%20would%20record%20audio%20cassettes%20from%20Kolkata%20and%20post%20them%20to%20Banerjee%20every%20couple%20of%20months.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20war%20is%20over%2C%20you%20will%20come%20to%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20refrain%20in%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sushmita%20reached%20her%20husband's%20home%2C%20she%20found%20that%20he%20had%20a%20first%20wife%2C%20Gulgutti%2C%20whom%20he%20married%2010%20years%20before%20her.%20Sushmita%20was%20stunned%2C%20but%20made%20peace%20with%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGulgutti%20was%20very%20quiet%2C%20shy%2C%20and%20nice.%20She%20used%20to%20call%20me%20Sahib%20Kamal%2C%26quot%3B%20Banerjee%20told%20Rediff.com%20in%202003.%20In%20her%20book%2C%20she%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3BSahib%20Kamal%26quot%3B%20probably%20meant%20%26quot%3BSahib%20ka%20Maal%26quot%3B%20(Sahib's%20Object%2FWoman).%20Banerjee%20lived%20with%20Gulgutti%2C%20her%20three%20brothers-in-law%20and%20their%20wives%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20Jaambaz%20in%20Kharana%20till%20Khan%20left%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThings%20soon%20took%20a%20turn%20for%20the%20worse%20as%20the%20Taliban's%20powers%20and%20insanity%20grew%20unchecked%20in%20Afghanistan.%20They%20made%20beards%20mandatory%20for%20men%20and%20made%20women%20invisible%20save%20for%20with%20their%20men.%20Newspapers%20were%20tossed%2C%20radio%20was%20banned%2C%20and%20books%20were%20made%20bonfires%20of.%20Men%20had%20to%20attend%20the%20mosque%20five%20times%20a%20day.%20Women%20could%20not%20go%20to%20the%20hospital%20lest%20a%20man%20touched%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Khan's%20home%2C%20Banerjee's%20days%20were%20all%20about%20%26quot%3Bno%20sleep%2C%20starvation%2C%20and%20physical%20assault%26quot%3B.%20The%20abuse%20by%20her%20brothers-in-law%20ranged%20from%20physical%20to%20mental.%20There%20was%20no%20end%20to%20it.%20%26quot%3BThey%20weren't%20human%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Banerjee%20in%20her%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20an%20unofficial%20prisoner%20here.%20Because%20this%20entire%20country%20is%20a%20jail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Village%20Doctor%20In%20The%20Eye%20Of%20The%20Taliban%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfghanistan%20barely%20had%20any%20women%20doctors.%20This%20usually%20meant%20no%20treatment%20for%20women.%20If%20they%20fell%20ill%2C%20they%20had%20to%20die%20at%20home%20since%20hospitals%20meant%20male%20doctors%20and%20no%20woman%20was%20authorised%20by%20the%20Taliban%20to%20be%20touched%20by%20anyone%20except%20her%20husband.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushmita%20had%20basic%20training%20in%20nursing.%20She%20had%20also%20read%20up%20a%20few%20books%20on%20gynaecology%20that%20came%20handy%20in%20those%20unreachable%20reaches%20of%20Afghanistan%2C%20where%20women%20depended%20on%20luck%20and%20limericks%20in%20the%20name%20of%20treatment.%20The%20Taliban%20had%20shut%20down%20all%20colleges.%20No%20one%20could%20study%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20under%20these%20circumstances%20that%20Banerjee%20opened%20her%20clinic%20and%20under%20that%20cover%2C%20spoke%20to%20women%20to%20make%20them%20aware%20of%20the%20injustice%20meted%20out%20to%20them.%20Her%20clinic%20was%20discovered%20by%20some%20men%20in%20May%201995.%20They%20beat%20her%20dead...%20well%2C%20almost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20attack%20on%20Banerjee%20prompted%20her%20to%20make%20up%20her%20mind%20about%20escaping%20Afghanistan%20and%20returning%20to%20Kolkata%2C%20where%20her%20family%20lived.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20planning%20an%20escape%20from%20the%20Taliban.%20It%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEscape%20From%20The%20Taliban%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%20Attempt%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Sushmita%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20few%20well-wishers%20that%20she%20had%20in%20the%20village%2C%20got%20herself%20a%20Jeep%20that%20took%20her%20to%20Islamabad%20in%20Pakistan.%20She%20knocked%20on%20the%20doors%20of%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%3B%20but%2C%20much%20to%20her%20shock%20and%20agony%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bhanded%20back%20to%20the%20Taliban%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecond%20Attempt%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Banerjee%20did%20not%20lose%20hope.%20She%20tried%20escaping%20the%20Taliban%20once%20again.%20%26quot%3BThis%20time%2C%20I%20ran%20all%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Banerjee%20wrote%20in%20her%20book.%20She%20was%20arrested%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20second%20attempt%20to%20escape%2C%20the%20Taliban%20decided%20they%20had%20had%20enough%20of%20this%20woman.%20A%20fatwa%20was%20issued.%20She%20was%20to%20die%20on%20July%2022%2C%201995.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThird%20Attempt%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20village%20headman%2C%20Dranai%20chacha%2C%20liked%20Sushmita%20for%20her%20social%20work.%20This%20man's%20son%20had%20been%20killed%20by%20the%20Taliban%2C%20so%20he%20had%20turned%20against%20them.%20On%20the%20day%20that%20Sushmita%20wanted%20to%20escape%20the%20Taliban%20for%20the%20third%20time%2C%20she%20grabbed%20an%20AK-47%20%26quot%3Band%20shot%20three%20Taliban%20men%26quot%3B%2C%20she%20recounted%20in%20her%20memoir.%20The%20headman%20helped%20her%20on%20to%20a%20Jeep%20and%20took%20her%20to%20Kabul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClose%20to%20Kabul%2C%20I%20was%20arrested.%20A%2015-member%20group%20of%20the%20Taliban%20interrogated%20me.%20Many%20of%20them%20said%20that%20since%20I%20had%20fled%20my%20husband's%20home%2C%20I%20should%20be%20executed.%20However%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20convince%20them%20that%20since%20I%20was%20an%20Indian%2C%20I%20had%20every%20right%20to%20go%20back%20to%20my%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Banerjee%20wrote%20in%20an%20article%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3EOutlook%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20interrogation%20continued%20through%20the%20night.%20The%20next%20morning%2C%20I%20was%20taken%20to%20the%20Indian%20embassy%2C%20from%20where%20I%20was%20given%20a%20safe%20passage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20handed%20a%20visa%20and%20passport%2C%20and%20she%20took%20off%20for%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20raining%20when%20her%20flight%20landed%20in%20the%20Indian%20capital.%20From%20there%2C%20she%20left%20for%20Kolkata%2C%20where%20she%20arrived%20on%20August%2012%2C%201995.%20Less%20than%20three%20months%20since%20the%20day%20she%20made%20up%20her%20mind%20to%20leave%20Afghanistan%2C%20she%20was%20in%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBack%20in%20Calcutta%2C%20I%20was%20re-united%20with%20my%20husband.%20I%20don't%20think%20he%20will%20ever%20be%20able%20to%20go%20back%20to%20his%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Banerjee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBack%20To%20Afghanistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20next%2018%20years%2C%20Sushmita%20Banerjee%20lived%20in%20India%20with%20her%20husband%20Jaambaz%20and%20worked%20on%20her%20books%2C%20a%20Bollywood%20film%20that%20starred%20Manisha%20Koirala%20(%3Cem%3EEscape%20From%20Taliban%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%202003)%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20for%20the%20women%20under%20the%20Taliban.%20She%20hoped%20her%20film%20would%20make%20it%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20and%20they%20would%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Banerjee%20celebrated%20Eid%20for%20a%20week%20in%20Kolkata%20and%20went%20back%20to%20her%20husband's%20home%20in%20Afghanistan.%20Khan%20had%20moved%20back%20home%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20Banerjee%20wanted%20to%20live%20with%20him.%20She%20had%20also%20converted%20to%20Islam%20by%20then%20and%20taken%20on%20a%20new%20name%2C%20%26quot%3BSayed%20Kamala%26quot%3B.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E25%20Bullets%20And%20A%20Silent%20Burial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Banerjee's%20return%20to%20Afghanistan%2C%20she%20resumed%20work%20as%20a%20health%20worker%20in%20the%20Paktika%20province.%20She%20was%20also%20filming%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20local%20women%20as%20part%20of%20her%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taliban%20got%20whiff%20of%20it.%20They%20showed%20up%20at%20Jaambaz's%20family%20home%20in%20Kharana%2C%20the%20provincial%20capital%20of%20Paktika%20on%20the%20night%20of%20September%204%2C%202013%2C%20and%20bound%20him%20up.%20Sushmita%20was%20dragged%20out%20and%20shot%20dead.%20They%20pumped%2025%20bullets%20into%20her%20body%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%2C%20and%20dumped%20it%20near%20a%20madrassa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanerjee's%20in-laws%20in%20Afghanistan%20buried%20her%20body%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-23984518%5C%22%3Eher%20brother%20in%20Kolkata%20wondered%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20s